{"comments":"Subsurface scattering layer for MaterialX Standard Surface.\n\nThe subsurface layer provides volumetric light scattering for translucent\nmaterials like skin, wax, marble, and milk. Light enters the surface,\nscatters internally, and exits at a different point.\n\n## MaterialX Parameters (from standard_surface.mtlx)\n\n- subsurface: [0.0, 1.0] default 0.0 — SSS weight (blend with diffuse)\n- subsurface_color: RGB default (1,1,1) — scattering color\n- subsurface_radius: RGB default (1,1,1) — mean free path per channel\n- subsurface_scale: [0.0, inf) default 1.0 — radius multiplier\n- subsurface_anisotropy: [-1.0, 1.0] default 0.0 — scattering direction\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Complete subsurface scattering layer configuration.\n\nFor skin, wax, marble, jade, milk, and other translucent materials.\nThe subsurface layer modifies the base diffuse to include volumetric\nscattering effects.\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["weight",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Spatial","Material","StandardSurface","Subsurface"],"SubsurfaceWeight"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["color",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Spatial","Material","StandardSurface","Subsurface"],"SubsurfaceColor"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["radius",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Spatial","Material","StandardSurface","Subsurface"],"SubsurfaceRadius"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["scale",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Spatial","Material","StandardSurface","Subsurface"],"SubsurfaceScale"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["anisotropy",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Spatial","Material","StandardSurface","Subsurface"],"SubsurfaceAnisotropy"